title: Best flavor
review: My family has come to love this flavor but it’s very hard to find in a traditional grocery/mass store anymore so have to buy online. They are pricier than when I could buy at the grocery but it’s worth the extra money for me as protein bars that everyone loves are hard to find.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2021
name: JANE M SMITH
title: Yummy
review: These are the best! I have been looking for these for a while,was surprised to find them here. These are a well balanced with protein, fat and carbs. Great in-between meals to eat.I wish they would get the get the caramel nut flavor in stocks. But this flavor is very delish!

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2021
name: Mom of 3.... Watson’s!
title: Alright
review: They were really hard to chew & they were not fresh. I have ate the Peanut Butter ones for years & tried a new flavor but wasn’t WOW’d by them. Had they not been so difficult to chew I would have probably ate them eventually but I did pack them for my husband who will eat anything (but he loves the PB ones and eats them everyday for breakfast on his way to base.) I packed this flavor for him & he usually tells me at night if he doesn’t want a specific item in his lunches again but for these he sent me a message and said never pack them bars again if we don’t have PB just don’t pack those bars!

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2021

title: Great!
review: My elderly mother (93) loves these. We try to get extra protein into her and she thinks she is eating peanut butter fudge.

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2021
name: justagal
title: Beware: received new package with product spoiled
review: I've been ordering these for years (make a great breakfast) and just got a 3pack where all the bars look like the pic. I tasted one without looking and thought that tasted weird, then took a good look at it - it is discolored and misshapen, and if it had melted and reformed. Opened all 3 boxes, and the same is true for all the bars. I don't know if this is a factory problem, or Amazon stored them incorrectly (it is not hot here, and they did not sit on my doorstep), but they are inedible and disgusting. Amazon refunded but i won't be buying them again anytime soon

review_data: Reviewed in the United States on April 23, 2021
name: Amazon Customer
title: Good for retreading your tires
review: Normally, the Yogurt Honey Peanut bars are delicious, but I knew I was "in trouble" as soon as I saw the expiration date.The date had not passed, but it is within a few weeks from receiving the items.For comparison, when purchased from a grocery store, the expiration date was well over a year out.But, I decided to try them anyway.They were slightly discolored, but the main problem was that I could literally not chew through these bars.I had ordered 3 boxes, so I open a bar from another box.Same problem.The bars were so hard that they could easily damage healthy teeth.Very disappointed.Given some of the positive reviews, I suppose your mileage may vary.But if need to drive a long distance, re-tread your tires with these bars, and your tires will last longer than your engine.
